
.TH HSH 1 "November 2024" "1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME

hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS

.B hsh

[command_string]

.SH DESCRIPTION

.B hsh

is a simple command interpreter that executes commands read from standard input or from a file.

.SH INVOCATION

.B hsh

can be invoked both interactively and non-interactively.

If invoked with standard input connected to a terminal,

.B hsh

displays a prompt and reads commands from the terminal.

.SH COMMAND EXECUTION

After receiving a command,

.B hsh

tokenizes it into words using spaces as delimiters.

The first word is the command, and the remaining words are arguments.

.B hsh

then searches for the command:

.RS

- If the command contains a slash (/), it is executed directly

.RE

.RS

- Otherwise, the shell searches for it in the directories listed in PATH

.RE

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS

.TP

.B exit

Exit the shell

.TP

.B env

Print the environment variables

.SH RETURN VALUE

.B hsh

returns the exit status of the last command executed.

.SH EXAMPLES

.PP

Interactive mode:

.RS

.nf

$ ./hsh

($) /bin/ls

hsh main.c shell.c

($) exit

$

.fi

.RE

.PP

Non-interactive mode:

.RS

.nf

$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh

hsh main.c shell.c

$

.fi

.RE

.SH SEE ALSO

sh(1), bash(1), dash(1)

.SH BUGS

No known bugs.

